<br>
If they are deep in the forests or the dungeons, I expect to see their travelling supplies and food/water drop too.<br>
<br>
So what if some if it is &quot;damaged&quot;, we should be able to loot the damaged items and be able to repair some of them.<br>
<br>
Used arrows should be recoverable or repairable. I recall in some RPG campaigns, we spent a good deal of time recycling metal arrowheads.<br>
<br>
If they wish to throw in some of this logistical &quot;realism&quot; - They should consider how people should be able to restock their supplies - Adventurers and scavengers should not have to go back to town - everything they need should be around.  Oh you need food, water?  Raid that little bandit encampment there and take what you need from their dead corpses and their supply tent - that's how they get their supplies most likely anyhow, by stealing it from someone else.<br>
<br>
